    "summary": "Wim Klaassen is Chief Consultant and Director of QUEST-Consult bv, the company he set up in 1992 to be involved with water sector reform with special attention for policy and institutionalisation of  IWRM/Basin management at national and regional level, change management, capacity development, management coaching, planning and monitoring. \nWim has broad international experience gained from nearly 30 years work in Europe, in Africa, the Middle East and Asia, including 10 years overseas residence in Tanzania, Kenya and Zimbabwe. \n\nHaving acquired an in-depth and multidisciplinary understanding of institutional and organisational development, Wim has developed into a water sector change management specialist. He also plans, evaluates and troubleshoots programmes that involve complex stakeholder relations and capacity-building requirements.  From 2011 -2016 he was appointed Strategic Advisor Water to  The Netherlands Embassies in Yemen and South Sudan. From 2018 to present he is Strategic Advisor for Water with the Netherlands Embassies in Ethiopia and South Sudan. \n\nWim's expert assignments typically involve advising on regulatory policy, institutional, organisational and policy development, capacity building and sustainability assurance. Wim usually acts in the role of team leader. He encourages strongly participatory approaches  and lays attention on human and cultural factors. Skill in coordinating with multiple stakeholders and related parties \u2013 at all levels \u2013 is one of his key capacities.\n\nWim is experienced in applying key change management models (Schein, LeKgotla) as well as the LogFrame and Project Cycle Management and formulating process and output indicators against a set timeline and benchmarks. He has key expertise in monitoring and evaluation procedures, both at institutional and programme level. For EuropAid 2003-09, he led a team to develop a Quality Tool for Results-Oriented Monitoring, resulting in an instrument that is now used by all EC-related regional ROM contractors and applied worldwide.",
